if she loses control.

263
00:20:21.360 --> 00:20:23.120
Well. I would never push my own kid.

264
00:20:25.000 --> 00:20:27.280
Our cover is blown. okay?

265
00:20:27.360 --> 00:20:29.680
If they catch her.
they're gonna lock her away.

266
00:20:30.120 --> 00:20:32.320
They're gonna run tests on her
for the rest of her life.

267
00:20:32.360 --> 00:20:34.416
They're gonna take her.
they're gonna put her in a cage.

268
00:20:34.440 --> 00:20:35.920
We'll never see her again. Vick.

269
00:20:36.000 --> 00:20:37.760
Who knows what's gonna happen to her?

270
00:20:39.520 --> 00:20:40.880
If who catches me?

271
00:20:43.760 --> 00:20:45.456
You're supposed
to be in your room. Charlie.

272
00:20:45.480 --> 00:20:46.520
You were yelling.

273
00:20:50.040 --> 00:20:51.656
Charlie. I need you
to go to your room right now

274
00:20:51.680 --> 00:20:52.760
okay. and pack a bag.

275
00:20:53.040 --> 00:20:55.136
- We're leaving in the morning.
- Sweetie. do you think...

276
00:20:55.160 --> 00:20:56.800
Are we bad people. Charlie?

277
00:20:59.240 --> 00:21:01.000
Do you know why
we have to move all the time?

278
00:21:03.560 --> 00:21:04.800
Because of your work.

279
00:21:05.360 --> 00:21:08.480
But also because
bad men are after us.

280
00:21:08.920 --> 00:21:09.920
Really bad.

281
00:21:10.200 --> 00:21:13.520
Because of the special things that
we can do. the pushing and the fire.

282
00:21:13.920 --> 00:21:16.360
And if they catch us.
they're gonna put us in jail.

283
00:21:16.440 --> 00:21:18.840
It's why we can't have
cell phones or Wi-Fi.

284
00:21:18.920 --> 00:21:20.200
Because they can track it.

285
00:21:20.800 --> 00:21:22.320
I'm sorry we lied to you.

286
00:21:23.440 --> 00:21:25.760
But I ran to the bathroom
so I wouldn't hurt anyone.

287
00:21:25.840 --> 00:21:28.760
That was the right thing to do.
Charlie. That was... that was right.

288
00:21:29.000 --> 00:21:31.480
I tried to throw it in the water.
but it didn't work.

289
00:21:31.960 --> 00:21:33.816
And now we're in trouble
and we're going to jail

290
00:21:33.840 --> 00:21:34.920
and it's all my fault!

291
00:21:35.000 --> 00:21:36.040
Okay. you gotta stay calm.

292
00:21:36.120 --> 00:21:37.736
- Calm down. Charlie.
- Just stay calm. sweetie.

293
00:21:37.760 --> 00:21:39.840
- You're okay.
- I'm not okay. Stop saying that.

294
00:21:39.920 --> 00:21:41.200
And I'm not special.

295
00:21:41.440 --> 00:21:42.640
I'm a monster!

296
00:21:42.720 --> 00:21:43.840
You are not a monster.

297
00:21:43.920 --> 00:21:44.976
- You just need to calm down.
- I'm a monster.

298
00:21:45.000 --> 00:21:46.416
- You're not. You're not a monster.
- I'm a monster.

299
00:21:46.440 --> 00:21:48.080
I'm a monster!

300
00:21:48.800 --> 00:21:49.800
Charlie.

301
00:21:50.040 --> 00:21:51.600
I hate living like this!

302
00:21:51.680 --> 00:21:52.720
Tough luck. Charlie.

303
00:21:52.800 --> 00:21:54.200
- This is who you are!
- Please.

304
00:21:54.280 --> 00:21:55.600
Andy. Stop.

305
00:21:55.680 --> 00:21:57.000
You made me this way.

306
00:21:58.280 --> 00:22:00.160
- Charlie. please!
- I hate who I am

307
00:22:00.240 --> 00:22:01.800
and I hate you!

308
00:22:02.760 --> 00:22:03.760
Charlie!

309
00:22:05.160 --> 00:22:06.160
Charlie!

310
00:22:10.280 --> 00:22:11.280
Oh. my God.

311
00:22:12.400 --> 00:22:13.400
Jesus Christ.

312
00:22:14.640 --> 00:22:17.920
I'm sorry. I'm sorry. I'm so sorry.

313
00:22:18.000 --> 00:22:20.720
Charlie. Charlie. no. Charlie. no.

314
00:22:21.200 --> 00:22:23.520
- Charlie.
- Charlie. no. I'm gonna be okay.

315
00:22:26.280 --> 00:22:27.280
She's okay.

316
00:22:27.600 --> 00:22:30.120
- <i>911. what is your emergency?</i>
- See? She's fine.

317
00:22:31.560 --> 00:22:32.680
- Come on.
- <i>Hello?</i>

318
00:22:32.760 --> 00:22:33.760
- Please.
- I'm okay.

319
00:22:33.840 --> 00:22:34.840
Hello?

320
00:22:35.840 --> 00:22:36.840
<i>Are you there?</i>

321
00:22:37.960 --> 00:22:39.000
Okay.

322
00:22:39.080 --> 00:22:40.800
It's okay. It's all right.

323
00:22:45.200 --> 00:22:46.680
It's okay. It's all right.

324
00:23:55.280 --> 00:23:56.400
<i>Is this Rainbird?</i>

325
00:23:57.320 --> 00:23:59.320
- Yes.
- This is Captain Jane Hollister

326
00:23:59.400 --> 00:24:00.400
DSI.

327
00:24:01.000 --> 00:24:02.880
I'm reactivating you. Rainbird.

328
00:24:05.640 --> 00:24:07.320
If that would be of interest.

329
00:24:07.760 --> 00:24:09.656
<i>Course it's still
the cleaning up other people's shit</i>

330
00:24:09.680 --> 00:24:11.400
just not literally.

331
00:24:14.160 --> 00:24:15.480
I left that life.

332
00:24:16.040 --> 00:24:17.680
<i>Yeah. and
how's that workin' out for ya?</i>

333
00:24:19.040 --> 00:24:20.200
<i>I know what happened.</i>

334
00:24:20.560 --> 00:24:23.920
The Shop used you up and
threw you out like unwanted trash.

335
00:24:24.680 --> 00:24:26.000
<i>And that wasn't right.</i>

336
00:24:27.520 --> 00:24:29.800
But that was the old guard.
I'm the new.

337
00:24:35.080 --> 00:24:36.680
Something's happened. Rainbird

338
00:24:36.760 --> 00:24:38.640
and I need it handled
with discretion.

339
00:24:38.720 --> 00:24:41.080
I understand that was your specialty.

340
00:24:47.600 --> 00:24:48.920
<i>What is the target?</i>

341
00:24:52.160 --> 00:24:56.680
Something for which
you are uniquely qualified.

342
00:24:58.480 --> 00:25:00.200
But unlike the others

343
00:25:01.080 --> 00:25:03.560
I need this quarry back alive.

344
00:25:05.200 --> 00:25:06.880
<i>Is that something you can handle?</i>

345
00:25:23.600 --> 00:25:24.600
Good job.

346
00:25:31.520 --> 00:25:32.520
There we go.

347
00:25:33.360 --> 00:25:34.360
You okay?

348
00:25:40.200 --> 00:25:41.760
Vick. this is bad.

349
00:25:44.840 --> 00:25:46.160
Ah. fuck.

350
00:25:46.440 --> 00:25:47.560
Almost done.

351
00:25:52.240 --> 00:25:53.240
That's it.

352
00:25:54.200 --> 00:25:55.480
You could've pushed her.

353
00:25:55.560 --> 00:25:59.240
We have no idea what's happening when
I'm going into those people's minds

354
00:25:59.320 --> 00:26:00.320
moving things around.

355
00:26:00.400 --> 00:26:02.016
Why would you ever want me
to do that to Charlie?

356
00:26:02.040 --> 00:26:03.040
What if I mess her up?

357
00:26:03.120 --> 00:26:04.240
And if she kills one of us?

358
00:26:04.320 --> 00:26:06.040
Don't fucking go there.

359
00:26:06.120 --> 00:26:07.120
Andy.

360
00:26:07.560 --> 00:26:10.200
This is what happens
when you stuff it down.

361
00:26:10.880 --> 00:26:12.200
It doesn't go away.

362
00:26:14.120 --> 00:26:16.096
Can you take her to the movies
or something. please?

363
00:26:16.120 --> 00:26:17.400
Ice cream or something?

364
00:26:23.400 --> 00:26:25.400
- Just get some rest. okay?
- Okay.

365
00:28:10.000 --> 00:28:11.000
Vicky McGee?

366
00:28:11.480 --> 00:28:14.520
I'm just following up on an
emergency call from earlier tonight.

367
00:28:15.040 --> 00:28:16.120
Oh. Yeah.

368
00:28:16.360 --> 00:28:17.720
It was a grease fire.

369
00:28:18.560 --> 00:28:20.720
On the stove.
My daughter overreacted.

370
00:28:21.160 --> 00:28:22.920
If you or your daughter need help...

371
00:28:23.000 --> 00:28:24.360
It's nothing like that.

372
00:28:26.000 --> 00:28:27.000
Honestly.

373
00:28:29.960 --> 00:28:32.880
You're sure about that.
you have a good night. then.

374
00:28:48.720 --> 00:28:50.480
Oh. Charlie.

375
00:29:05.240 --> 00:29:06.400
Where did they go?

376
00:29:07.680 --> 00:29:10.680
Your husband and the girl.

377
00:29:15.360 --> 00:29:18.680
<i>Ice cream. Movies.</i>

378
00:29:22.000 --> 00:29:23.200
Ice cream...

379
00:29:24.840 --> 00:29:26.120
or the movies?

380
00:29:30.520 --> 00:29:32.120
Did you think you were unique?

381
00:29:32.880 --> 00:29:35.920
Before they tested their poison
on pretty. young coeds

382
00:29:36.280 --> 00:29:38.000
they had to use the lab rats.

383
00:29:46.040 --> 00:29:47.520
And you're out of practice.

384
00:30:26.200 --> 00:30:27.400
How could you work for them?

385
00:30:27.800 --> 00:30:29.480
Help them after what they did to you?

386
00:30:29.920 --> 00:30:32.640
Come peacefully. and you'll live.

387
00:30:32.920 --> 00:30:35.160
I will die before
I let them have her.

388
00:30:35.240 --> 00:30:38.320
Your life. to them.
is a secondary concern.

389
00:30:38.680 --> 00:30:39.680
And yours?

390
00:31:03.240 --> 00:31:06.520
When you see her. you'll understand.

391
00:31:06.920 --> 00:31:08.200
And you will regret.

392
00:31:19.680 --> 00:31:21.360
Do you think she'll forgive me?

393
00:31:25.000 --> 00:31:26.200
Well. she's your mom.

394
00:31:26.760 --> 00:31:28.200
She'll always forgive you.

395
00:31:29.400 --> 00:31:30.400
No matter what.

396
00:31:33.880 --> 00:31:35.680
It was supposed to be you.

397
00:31:36.400 --> 00:31:37.400
What?

398
00:31:42.360 --> 00:31:43.880
It was supposed to be you.

399
00:32:01.960 --> 00:32:03.080
I feel weird.

400
00:32:04.320 --> 00:32:05.760
Too much Rocky Road.

401
00:32:07.480 --> 00:32:09.296
She's probably asleep.
I'm gonna check on her. okay?

402
00:32:09.320 --> 00:32:10.680
Here. take that to the trash.

403
00:32:11.160 --> 00:32:12.640
And then throw on
your PJs. all right?

404
00:32:32.680 --> 00:32:33.680
- Surrender.
- Charlie?

405
00:32:33.760 --> 00:32:34.760
Daddy.

406
00:32:35.400 --> 00:32:36.640
No one gets hurt.

407
00:32:41.160 --> 00:32:42.240
Let her go.

408
00:32:44.000 --> 00:32:45.560
You know what it costs. don't you?

409
00:32:46.880 --> 00:32:48.120
To hurt someone.

410
00:32:48.320 --> 00:32:49.560
To take a life.

411
00:32:50.080 --> 00:32:52.040
Would you ask that of your own child?

412
00:32:55.720 --> 00:32:56.840
Do you feel that?

413
00:32:57.480 --> 00:32:59.200
Let her go.
or it's gonna get a lot worse.

414
00:33:00.240 --> 00:33:02.560
- Where's Mommy?
- She has no aim without sight

415
00:33:02.640 --> 00:33:04.040
if she's like the rest of us.

416
00:33:04.120 --> 00:33:05.200
Where's my wife?

417
00:33:10.840 --> 00:33:11.880
Where's Mommy?

418
00:33:14.720 --> 00:33:15.880
I don't know. sweetheart.

419
00:33:16.640 --> 00:33:17.640
Yes. you do.

420
00:33:18.040 --> 00:33:19.800
Where's Mommy? Tell me now!

421
00:33:23.000 --> 00:33:24.000
Mom?

422
00:33:35.080 --> 00:33:37.600
Come here. Run. Run. Charlie!

423
00:33:40.200 --> 00:33:41.480
- Run!
- Mommy!

424
00:33:57.600 --> 00:33:59.520
Come on. We have
to get somewhere safe.

425
00:34:18.960 --> 00:34:21.600
Doctor Wanless. you have a guest.

426
00:34:24.080 --> 00:34:25.400
Good morning. Joseph.

427
00:34:26.600 --> 00:34:27.880
I brought you something.

428
00:34:30.200 --> 00:34:31.720
Your favorite colors. too.

429
00:34:38.840 --> 00:34:41.520
I'm Captain Hollister.
newly appointed. DSI.

430
00:34:41.880 --> 00:34:44.680
Why are you here?

431
00:34:45.480 --> 00:34:46.640
Captain?

432
00:34:46.920 --> 00:34:49.320
I made calls to your predecessor.

433
00:34:49.680 --> 00:34:51.400
They went unanswered.

434
00:34:52.680 --> 00:34:59.120
But now. they stuff a new face
into the same old suit

435
00:34:59.480 --> 00:35:02.040
and that face just comes...

436
00:35:03.160 --> 00:35:04.480
knocking on my door!

437
00:35:04.560 --> 00:35:06.120
With all due respect. Doctor

438
00:35:06.280 --> 00:35:08.680
Captain McConnell doesn't
have the legs for this outfit.

439
00:35:09.240 --> 00:35:11.360
Completely oblivious

440
00:35:11.560 --> 00:35:15.200
to the dire nature
of the situation we've created.

441
00:35:15.280 --> 00:35:16.360
We found them.

442
00:35:17.120 --> 00:35:18.160
Joseph.

443
00:35:20.000 --> 00:35:21.040
Shall we talk?

444
00:35:29.320 --> 00:35:30.720
<i>When you see her</i>

445
00:35:31.280 --> 00:35:32.800
<i>you'll understand</i>

446
00:35:33.000 --> 00:35:34.440
<i>and you will regret.</i>

447
00:35:47.000 --> 00:35:49.280
I miss you. Mom. I'll get 'em.

448
00:36:12.600 --> 00:36:13.600
Let's see.

449
00:37:08.240 --> 00:37:10.800
Oh. Hi! Hi. kitty. kitty.

450
00:37:12.120 --> 00:37:13.120
Hi.

451
00:37:14.000 --> 00:37:15.200
Come here. kitty. kitty.

452
00:37:15.920 --> 00:37:17.080
Come here. It's okay.

453
00:37:17.840 --> 00:37:19.000
Don't run away. Come on.

454
00:37:19.760 --> 00:37:21.040
It's okay. I'm nice.

455
00:37:21.960 --> 00:37:23.000
I won't hurt you.

456
00:37:28.640 --> 00:37:29.640
Charlie?

457
00:37:32.600 --> 00:37:33.640
Charlie?

458
00:37:38.600 --> 00:37:39.920
He scratched me.

459
00:37:44.920 --> 00:37:46.080
Honey. he's in pain.

460
00:37:47.640 --> 00:37:49.560
You have to put him
out of his misery. all right?

461
00:37:50.680 --> 00:37:52.480
I really didn't mean to.

462
00:37:52.800 --> 00:37:54.480
I know you didn't. I know.

463
00:37:55.920 --> 00:37:57.400
This is what it costs. though.

464
00:38:01.040 --> 00:38:02.760
'Cause it can't be
a reaction like that.

465
00:38:02.840 --> 00:38:03.840
It's gotta be...

466
00:38:05.240 --> 00:38:06.240
a decision.

467
00:38:07.000 --> 00:38:08.520
That's the only way
you can control it.

468
00:38:09.680 --> 00:38:10.680
You can do it.

469
00:38:31.120 --> 00:38:32.120
Good job.

470
00:38:37.760 --> 00:38:39.000
I want to help her.

471
00:38:39.480 --> 00:38:40.960
You want to use her.

472
00:38:41.120 --> 00:38:43.120
The girl. she can't help what she is.

473
00:38:43.200 --> 00:38:46.880
The poor thing. she's been
brain-fucked from birth.

474
00:38:47.320 --> 00:38:50.760
This is a chance
to turn a past failure

475
00:38:51.000 --> 00:38:52.520
into present success.

476
00:38:52.760 --> 00:38:54.320
I want you to come back to work

477
00:38:55.320 --> 00:38:56.520
Doctor Wanless.

478
00:38:59.120 --> 00:39:02.800
How hard must it have been for them?

479
00:39:03.200 --> 00:39:05.000
The parents. when the girl was born?

480
00:39:05.680 --> 00:39:07.640
The bottle is late.

481
00:39:08.240 --> 00:39:09.800
The baby cries.

482
00:39:10.320 --> 00:39:15.040
And a Teddy bear bursts into flames.

483
00:39:16.200 --> 00:39:17.600
Right there.

484
00:39:18.320 --> 00:39:20.800
In the crib. beside her.

485
00:39:21.280 --> 00:39:24.120
Can you imagine their fear?

486
00:39:25.600 --> 00:39:27.920
And it's awful. that's really...
What's your point?

487
00:39:29.120 --> 00:39:33.000
The girl's power is in its infancy.

488
00:39:34.800 --> 00:39:36.320
Terrible. yes. but

489
00:39:37.200 --> 00:39:40.240
trivial compared to what's coming.

490
00:39:41.280 --> 00:39:45.120
But she's growing. our little girl.

491
00:39:46.040 --> 00:39:49.320
She is becoming a young woman.

492
00:39:49.960 --> 00:39:54.080
And someday soon.
the power will grow too.

493
00:39:54.160 --> 00:39:55.800
Perhaps it already has.

494
00:39:58.000 --> 00:40:03.000
And then. one day.
she may be capable...

495
00:40:05.080 --> 00:40:08.800
of creating a nuclear explosion

496
00:40:09.240 --> 00:40:12.520
simply with the force of her mind.

497
00:40:12.920 --> 00:40:17.800
Doctor. we built a facility
especially for people like Charlie.

498
00:40:18.160 --> 00:40:19.640
We can teach her.

499
00:40:20.000 --> 00:40:21.240
We can train her.

500
00:40:21.320 --> 00:40:23.280
You can exploit her.

501
00:40:23.360 --> 00:40:25.000
Don't you lecture me on morality.

502
00:40:25.520 --> 00:40:28.440
You developed Lot Six.
You gave it to those kids.

503
00:40:28.520 --> 00:40:29.760
And it was a mistake!

504
00:40:29.840 --> 00:40:31.640
Well. that's too fuckin' bad!

505
00:40:32.280 --> 00:40:33.400
It's done!

506
00:40:34.520 --> 00:40:36.480
Jesus. We're not gonna clone her.

507
00:40:36.800 --> 00:40:39.080
We're not gonna make
a little army of Charlies.

508
00:40:39.160 --> 00:40:40.160
We just... We...

509
00:40:42.400 --> 00:40:44.120
We want to understand her.

510
00:40:47.600 --> 00:40:49.240
She's the first of her kind.

511
00:40:49.760 --> 00:40:52.200
And no one understands her
better than you.

512
00:40:52.920 --> 00:40:54.920
The man who made the serum.

513
00:40:55.160 --> 00:40:58.320
You're the father of it all.

514
00:40:59.400 --> 00:41:00.400
What do you say?

515
00:41:06.920 --> 00:41:11.600
There are none so blind
as those who will not see.

516
00:41:14.320 --> 00:41:15.320
What?

517
00:41:18.400 --> 00:41:19.680
Heed my words...

518
00:41:21.160 --> 00:41:22.400
very carefully.

519
00:41:25.040 --> 00:41:26.280
Terminate the girl.

520
00:41:27.240 --> 00:41:30.200
Or one day. she will destroy us all.

521
00:41:30.280 --> 00:41:31.280
Do you hear me?

522
00:41:33.360 --> 00:41:35.200
Terminate her.

523
00:41:37.440 --> 00:41:39.560
I hoped this would've gone better.

524
00:41:44.880 --> 00:41:45.880
That's good.

525
00:41:46.920 --> 00:41:47.960
Can we pray?

526
00:41:50.280 --> 00:41:52.160
Yeah. Sure. we can pray.

527
00:41:54.200 --> 00:41:55.200
All right.

528
00:41:58.200 --> 00:41:59.240
Dear god...

529
00:42:00.760 --> 00:42:02.160
please let this...

530
00:42:02.920 --> 00:42:05.480
cat be happy...

531
00:42:05.560 --> 00:42:06.760
in cat heaven.

532
00:42:07.160 --> 00:42:11.400
And just. you know.
make sure that he...

533
00:42:12.400 --> 00:42:13.400
or she...

